Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2016=20patch=200073=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20Surface=20INDEX8=20+=208bpp=20blit=20primitives?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the Lever-3 indexed-mode renderer path. When data/master.pal +
data/master.palmap are present (built by tools/build-master-palette.py
in sub-phase 16.1) and SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8 is not "0"
(kill switch), Surface::loadImage produces INDEX8 surfaces backed by
the master palette and the hand-rolled blit primitives dispatch on
window-surface format.

Surface (src/graphics/Surface.{h,cpp}):
  * surface16bpp() → surfaceCpu(), colorkey16() → colorkey() returning
    Uint32 (low 8 bits hold INDEX8 byte; low 16 bits hold RGB565 word)
  * pixelFormat() accessor added
  * _surface_rgb565 → _surface_cpu, _colorkey16 → _colorkey
  * loadImage / loadFromSDLSurface grow INDEX8 branches: indexed
    sources walk the per-asset remap LUT from master.palmap; truecolor
    sources (or assets without a palmap entry) take a per-pixel
    nearest-master-color path with a small one-shot 5/6/5-quantized
    cache so the 320×240 truecolor backgrounds load in ~50 ms not
    seconds.

Renderer (src/graphics/Renderer.{h,cpp}):
  * _indexed_mode + _master_palette + _palmap_cache members + public
    accessors indexedMode(), masterPalette(), paletteRemapFor()
  * _load_master_palette / _load_master_palmap: read the formats frozen
    in /tmp/wave-16-1-palette-format.md §1+§2; gracefully fall back to
    wave-15 RGB565 on any IO/version mismatch
  * _blit_indexed + _blit_indexed_mirrored: byte-per-pixel siblings of
    the wave-12.1/12.3 RGB565 primitives. Same dst-clip pattern.
  * _packed_index_for: small static cache + weighted-Euclidean nearest-
    color search; used by clearScreen / fillRect / drawRect / drawLine
    INDEX8 arms
  * _try_fast_blit + _try_fast_blit_mirrored: format gate widened to
    accept INDEX8↔INDEX8 (matched src/dst); dispatches to either the
    RGB565 or INDEX8 primitive
  * _ensure_handrolled_surface: gate widened symmetrically
  * clearScreen / fillRect / drawRect / drawLine: per-format dispatch
    with SDL_memset-based byte fills on the INDEX8 arm
  * Slow-reason histogram updated to count "neither RGB565 nor INDEX8"
    as the format bucket

Wave-16-3 (patch 0072) flipped SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP to "8" already; this
patch makes the renderer produce the matching INDEX8 surfaces. Without
master.pal/master.palmap the renderer logs an error and falls back to
RGB565 — the kill-switch path still works (SDL3-DOS will then pick the
highest-bpp <= 8 mode it can find, which the SW renderer handles via
the slow-path SDL_RenderTexture).

Out of scope for this patch (deferred to 0074): cmod LUT + 8bpp
drawSurfaceColorMod dispatch.

